==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: American sign language
<hw>American sign language</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a sign language, used
in the United States mostly by the deaf or for communication with the
deaf, in which gestures made with the hands symbolize words,
alphabetical letters, or ideas, permitting rapid communication in the
absence of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Ameslan.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ames-ace</ent>⟦br⟧
